Selenium WebDriver – Driver Methods (Browser Commands)

get()
Used to load a new webpage in the current browser window by passing a URL.

getCurrentURL()
Returns the URL of the currently opened webpage.

getPageSource()
Returns the HTML source code of the current webpage.

getTitle()
Returns the title text of the current page.

close() vs quit()
close() closes the currently active browser tab/window.
quit() closes all opened browser windows and ends the driver session.

getWindowHandle()
Returns the unique window ID of the currently active browser window.

getWindowHandles()
Returns a set of unique IDs for all opened browser windows.

navigate()
Supports browser navigation:
navigate().to(), navigate().back(), navigate().forward(), navigate().refresh()

switchTo()
Switches WebDriver control to another window, frame, or alert.

Selenium WebDriver – WebElement Methods (Element Commands)

sendKeys()
Types text into an input field or editable area.

clear()
Clears existing text inside an input field.

click()
Performs click action on a button, link, or any clickable element.

findElement()
Returns the first matching WebElement based on a locator.

findElements()
Returns a list of all matching WebElements as per locator.

getDomAttribute()
Returns the live DOM attribute value of the element.

getScreenShotAs()
Takes a screenshot of a specific element only (not entire page).

getText()
Extracts visible text inside the element.

isDisplayed()
Returns true/false depending on element visibility on the page.

isEnabled()
Returns true/false depending on whether the element is active for use.

isSelected()
Returns true/false if checkbox/radio/option is selected.